    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed the required level for Medium model risk. The single deficiency (Test conditions, achieved level 1 vs. required level 2) is offset by the strong quantitative output comparison results (all E/uval < 1.96) and the direct equivalence between validation and COU configuration. The overall credibility evidence is sufficient to support regulatory submission of the non-cannulated pedicle screw FEA model.",
